==Pyrenees== There are annual bear festivals that take place in various towns and communes in the Pyrenees region.
In [[Prats-de-Mollo-la-Preste|Prats-de-Mollo]], the {{illm|Fête de l’ours de Prats-de-Mollo-la-Preste{{!}}''Fête de l'Ours''|fr|Fête de l’ours de Prats-de-Mollo-la-Preste}} ("festival of the bear") held on [[Candlemas]] (February 2) is a ritual in which men dressed up as bears brandishing sticks terrorize people in the streets.<ref>{{citation|last=Webb |first=Mick |title=Bear Mountain: The battle to save the Pyrenean brown bear |publisher=Guardian Books |year=n.d. |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=Kp-bBAAAQBAJ&pg=PT6 |pages=<!--unpaginated-->}}</ref> Formerly, the festival centered on the "bears" mock-attacking the women and trying to blacken their breasts (with soot), which seemed scandalous to outside first-time observers. But according to the testimony of someone who remembered the olden days before that, the festival that at Prats-de-Mollo involved elaborate staging, much like the version in [[Arles-sur-Tech|Arles]].<ref name=fabre>{{citation|last=Fabre |first=Daniel |title=Recherches sur Jean de l'Ours (2e partie)|journal=Folklore: revue d'ethnographie méridonale| volume=XXII |number=134 |year=1969 |url=http://garae.fr/Folklore/R52_134_ETE_1969.pdf |pages=10–11<!--2-41-->}}</ref>
The [[Arles-sur-Tech]] version ({{illm|Fête de l’ours d’Arles-sur-Tech{{!}}''Fête de l’ours d’Arles-sur-Tech''|fr|Fête de l’ours d’Arles-sur-Tech}}) involves a female character named Rosetta (Roseta) who gets abducted by the "bear". Rosetta was traditionally played by a man or a boy dressed up as a girl.<!--Mr. Mackintosh was writing in 1923~1927; they seem to use pantomime props now.--> The "bear" would bring the Rosetta to a hut raised on the center square of town (where the victim would be fed sausages, cake, and white wine). The event finished with the "bear" being shaved and "killed".<ref>{{citation|editor-last=Crichton |editor-first=Robin |title=Monsieur Mackintosh: the travels and paintings of Charles Rennie Mackintosh in the Pyrénées Orientales, 1923-1927 |publisher=Luath |year=2007 |url=https://books.google.co.jp/books?hl=ja&id=7YNIAQAAIAAJ |page=41<!--unpaginated-->}}</ref><ref name=fabre/>
A well-known bear festival also occurs at Haute-Vallespir ({{illm|Fêtes de l'ours en Vallespir{{!}}''Fêtes de l'ours en Vallespir''|fr|Fêtes de l'ours en Vallespir}}).<ref name=fabre/>
