The '''Carmacks Group''' is a [[Late Cretaceous]] [[volcanic group]] in southwest-central [[Yukon]], Canada, located between the communities of [[Dawson City]] and [[Whitehorse, Yukon|Whitehorse]]. It consists of [[flood basalt]]s, coarse volcaniclastic rocks and sandy [[tuff]]s interbedded with [[subordinate]] [[andesite]] and [[basalt]]ic lava flows.<ref name="VB">{{cite paper|title=Yellowstone in Yukon: The Late Cretaceous Carmacks Group|last1=Johnson|first1=Stehen T.|last2=Wynne|first2=P. Jane|last3=Hart|first3=Craig J. R.|last4=Enkin|first4=Randolph J.|last5=Engebretson|first5=David C.|publisher=[[Geological Society of America]]|volume=24|page=998|year=1996|issn=0091-7613}}</ref> It has been interpreted to be a displaced portion of the [[Yellowstone hotspot]] track that was formed 70&nbsp;million years ago.<ref name="VB"/>

